snippet.textDisplay:
Let me set the record straight and add my two cents. The NBA dragged it's feet and waited until the horse escaped the barn. They are a day late and a dollar short. The NBA is a multi billion dollar business and they should have had the players tested much earlier. If China has been testing people for months now, why couldn't the league get test kits long before now? Believe me, more NBA players are going to test positive going forward. They are asking the teams that played against the Jazz to voluntarily quarantine, however what about the teams that played against the teams who played against the Jazz. Players sweat on each other. It's not just coughing or
sneezing etc., the players are exchanging bodily fluids. They are more vulnerable to being infected. Gobert is young, so young people can get the coronavirus also.
Moreover the young people that get infected can infect more vulnerable people such as seniors and less healthy people. They are carriers. This brings me to the point of, why are the public schools still open? Do they wait until multitudes of children are infected? If the colleges are suspending classes, why are the lower grade schools still open? These younger people can get infected and bring it home to their senior parents and grandparents etc.
